body:
@alice-i-cecile @cart I noticed that @ickshonpe mentioned running into a similar problem running the feathers example (it's mentioned in the focus rings PR).

As I'm not a windows user, I can't reproduce this myself. However, from the description given above, it sounds like it's not a problem specific to feathers but rather a consequence of the new spawning API using lots of stack when spawning a complex nested hierarchy.

I'd hate to ship the milestone with this bug: it doesn't look good if users want to try out the shiny new example and it immediately crashes. I can, of course, cut down on the size of the demo, but we should probably investigate the root cause a bit first.
